==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bryonin
<hw>Bry"o*nin</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A bitter principle obtained from the root of the bryony
(<spn>Bryonia alba</spn> and <spn>Bryonia dioica</spn>). It is a white,
or slightly colored, substance, and is emetic and cathartic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

